article.description: Coppin St. holds off Bethune-Cookman 64-60 in MEAC 1st round
article.headline: Coppin St. holds off Bethune-Cookman 64-60 in MEAC 1st round
article.linkText: Coppin St. holds off Bethune-Cookman 64-60 in MEAC 1st round
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Sterling Smith had 14 points, Daquan Brickhouse made two game-clinching free throws with two seconds left and ninth-seeded Coppin State beat No. 8 seed Bethune-Cookman 64-60 on Tuesday in the first round of the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference tournament. The teams have met in the opening round each of the past three seasons -- with Coppin State winning two straight. Coppin State will play top-seeded North Carolina Central (24-6), the reigning tournament champions, on Wednesday in the quarterfinals. Brickhouse finished with eight points for Coppin State (8-22), including an off-balance 3-pointer with the shot clock winding down for a 60-53 lead with 3:04 left. Ricky Johnson led Bethune-Cookman (11-21) with 21 points. Denzel Dulin had 16 points with seven rebounds. Bethune-Cookman trailed by nine points, its biggest deficit of the game, until Quintin Brewer made a hook shot in the paint and Mikel Trapp buried a 3-pointer to pull within 45-41 with 10:42 left.
